{{Infobox news event | title = 2014 GAIL Gas Pipeline Tragedy | image = | image_size = | caption = | date = {{start date|2014|06|27}} | time = 05:30 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] | place = [[Nagaram, East Godavari district|Nagaram]], [[East Godavari District]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]] | coordinates = {{coord|16.501106|N|81.910726|E|type:event_region:IN|display=inline,title}} | also known as = | cause = 18" Gas Pipeline rupture | reported injuries = 30 | reported death(s) = 22 }}
On June 27, 2014 a massive fire broke out following a blast in [[Gas Authority of India Limited]] (GAIL) 18" size underground gas Pipeline<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/blast-at-a-gail-gas-pipeline-in-andhra-pradesh-14-dead/482107-62-127.html |title=Blast at a GAIL gas pipeline in Andhra Pradesh, 14 dead:IBNLive Videos |publisher=Ibnlive.in.com |date= |accessdate=2016-01-18}}</ref> at [[Nagaram, East Godavari district]]in [[East Godavari district]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]], India.<ref>{{cite web|title=GAIL Pipeline Blast in Andhra Pradesh kills 22, over 30 injured|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/06/ongc-pipeline-blast-in-andhra-pradesh-kills-over-11/|work=IANS|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|accessdate=27 June 2014}}</ref> The accident took place near [[Tatipaka|Tatipaka refinery]] of [[Oil and Natural Gas Corporation]] (ONGC), about 180&nbsp;km from state capital [[Vijayawada]].<ref>[http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-gail-gas-pipeline-explosion-14-dead-several-injured-oil-minister-constitutes-committee-to-probe-1998115 GAIL gas pipeline explosion: 14 dead, several injured; Lighting of stove might have sparked fire, say Police | Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-28052104 BBC News - Fourteen killed in India gas pipeline blast<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
==Casualties== About 18 people were reportedly killed and over 40 injured in the accident. The injured were shifted to hospitals at [[Amalapuram]] and [[Kakinada]] towns.
==Accident== State Finance Minister [[Yanamala Rama Krishnudu]] told reporters that 22 people were killed and many others were injured when the fire broke out around 5.30 a.m. in Nagaram village in Mamidikuduru mandal of the coastal district. The minister said: “The fire caused massive losses. Coconut trees, other crops, cattle and wild birds in over 10 acres were reduced to ashes.”
